description: {"blocks":[{"key":"cmpj2","text":"This protocol uses a python based script and command-line blastn to annotate Sanger sequencing results from genome amplifications. Its main use in our lab (https://biocomputationlab.com) is to identify the location and gene locus of transposon inserts in microbial bacterial genomes of Pseudomonas putida KT2440.
